					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Gradualore wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You can import a 256x240 source bitmap, and it finds an optimal palette (if possible with the input bitmap)</div>
<br />The basic problem is as follows: Given 240 sets I of 4 colors, find four sets P of 4 colors (∀p #P[p] = 4) such that one backdrop color B is in all P (∀p∃B B ∈ P[p]), and each I is a subset of some P (∀i∃p I[i] ⊆ P[p]) I was hung up on 1. how to construct P efficiently, and 2. what to do if P does not exist, such as trying to dither a photo down to NES specs.</div>

